responses: {"Q0":"Only in a 50-50 situation would I choose the unknown box due to it having a higher chance of either gaining a dollar or nothing in comparison to just having a 50-50 chance. If my chances of winning a dollar is already known to be higher, even just by five balls, then I would rather choose the known box. \nDuring the first experiment, the red side has a certain chance of gaining 48 to 51 points whereas blue side results in very high or very low points, maybe depending on the balls texture."}
